article.headline: Manhattan 73, Rider 68
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Manhattan 73, Rider 68. NEW YORK -- Darryl Crawford and Patrick Bouli hit consecutive 3-pointers in the last 1:38 and Manhattan scored the final 10 points of the game in a 73-68 victory over Rider on Sunday. Crawford finished with 26 points for the Jaspers (15-11, 9-7 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won four of five. Chris Smith had 12 points and 11 rebounds for Manhattan. Mike Ringgold and Justin Robinson both scored 18 points for the Broncs (14-11, 9-6), while Ryan Thompson added 16. Rider took a 68-63 lead when Thompson scored with 3 minutes to go. A basket by Lawrence Jolicouer followed by a 3 by Crawford with 1:38 left tied the game at 68. Bouli hit the go-ahead 3-pointer with 49.5 seconds remaining. Rider missed two 3-point attempts with the clock winding down, and Crawford concluded the scoring with two free throws with 4.3 seconds to go.
